      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="7f2445d0-0e73-4b65-b7bf-a1d354bffc42" type="Noun">
          <Vi>Định giá; sự định giá; giá trị ước lượng</Vi>
          <En>The process of determining the worth or value of something, especially property, assets, or a business</En>
          <Example>The company hired an independent appraiser to conduct the valuation of its intellectual property.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="2d8d03f4-13b7-4052-bca2-d82b7a311e0a">
              <Vi>Trong giao dịch mua bán doanh nghiệp, định giá là bước quan trọng để xác định mức giá hợp lý.</Vi>
              <En>In a business acquisition, valuation is a crucial step to determine a fair price.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="e3f5d103-a49a-4cd8-8a0f-eb80ab6b82e1">
              <Vi>Ngân hàng yêu cầu định giá tài sản bảo đảm trước khi cấp khoản vay.</Vi>
              <En>The bank requires a property valuation before approving a loan.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
